{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #939: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $r\\geq 2$. An $r$-powerful number $n$ is one such that if $p\\mid n$ then $p^r\\mid n$.\n\nIf $r\\geq 4$ then can the sum of $r-2$ coprime $r$-powerful numbers ever be itself $r$-powerful? Are there at most finitely many such solutions?\n\nAre there infinitely many triples of coprime $3$-powerful numbers $a,b,c$ such that $a+b=c$? Prize: no. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_6b6fa66eccd5a5aa","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos939.erdos_939 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos939.erdos_939.","id":"vf_7b33e365509cb280","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/939.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_6b6fa66eccd5a5aa","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:939","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_7b33e365509cb280","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:939","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_7b33e365509cb280","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_6b6fa66eccd5a5aa","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0a25edabc16db143","frontier_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","label":"Erd